The paper deals with error correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The construction of these codes involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), as well as combinatorics (cs.DC) and complexity theory (cs.CC). The Poisson repeat channel is a stochastic process, which falls under the category of statistical inference (cs.SI).
